MUSHROOM POISONING - RUSSIA (NIZHNIY NOVGOROD) (02)
***************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail, a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
Date 2 Sep 2006
From: Jane Canestra <Jane.Canestra@dhs.vic.gov.au>

Regarding the toxicity of Boletus species, the US Food and Drug
Administration Bad Bug Book lists an example of Boletus species, _Boletus
piperatus_, as containing a toxin which is a gastrointestinal irritant, of
which the chemistry is virtually unknown. The link follows:
<http://www.cfsan.fda.gov/~mow/chap40.html>.
--
Dr Jane Canestra MBBS FACEM
CBR Liaison
Program Coordination
Public Health Branch
Department of Human Services, Victoria
50 Lonsdale Street, Melbourne VIC 3001
<jane.canestra@dhs.vic.gov.au>
<http://www.health.vic.gov.au/phtopics/index.htm>
[I appreciate Dr Canestra pointing out a website and citation I missed. It
seems to be well recognized as a gastrointestinal irritant, but again the
toxin itself is ill characterized.- Mod.TG]
